## Codex Guardrails (User Confirmation Required)

- Never run `git commit` unless the user explicitly asks in the current thread.
- Never run `git push` (including pushing tags) unless the user explicitly asks in the current thread, or the current thread clearly treats `commit + push` as one bundled action.
- Default interpretation in this repo: when the user asks to "commit", treat it as `commit + push` unless they explicitly say `commit only`, `no push`, or equivalent.
- If asked to commit under the default bundled flow: show `git status --porcelain` and `git diff --stat`, propose an exact commit message, state the exact remote + branch/ref to be pushed, then wait for one explicit confirmation before running both `git commit` and `git push`.
- If the user explicitly asks for `commit only`: show `git status --porcelain` and `git diff --stat`, propose an exact commit message, then wait for explicit confirmation before running `git commit` only.
- Commit message standard (required):
  - Subject format: `<type>(<scope>): <summary>` (or `<type>: <summary>` if no scope), and keep subject <= 72 chars.
  - For non-trivial commits, include sections: `Why`, `Changes`, `Validation`, `Risk`.
- If asked to push as a standalone action: state the exact remote + branch/ref to be pushed, then wait for explicit confirmation before running `git push`.
<!-- CODEX:END user-approval-guardrails -->

## 变更策略

- 结构调整优先用 `git mv`
- 保持 diff 最小化，不做无意义大格式化
- 文档与结构不一致时，以当前结构为准并修正文档

## 常用自检

- 查 legacy 命名残留：`rg -n "active/|portable/|native/|core/" .`
- 检查 master-schedule 脚本：`python3 -m py_compile 06_Infra/plugins/master-schedule/scripts/*.py`
- 检查本地转录插件：`python3 -m py_compile plugins/memo-audio-transcribe/scripts/*.py`
- 检查 lark-bridge shell：`bash -n 06_Infra/plugins/lark-bridge/scripts/*.sh`
- 检查 Network CLI：`python3 -m py_compile 05_Resources/network/_cli/network.py 05_Resources/network/_cli/validate_people.py`
- 语言切换 dry-run：`python3 06_Infra/i18n/switch_language.py --lang en`
- 示例清理 dry-run：`python3 06_Infra/cleanup_examples.py`
